<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1908/513454-625x325.jpg" alt="Image source: Gallo/Getty." width="625" height="325">Image source: Gallo/Getty.My.T Money wants to be a reliable and secure alternative to cash transactions that works regardless of the mobile operator in Mauritius. To benefit from this service, it will be enough to visit a Telecom shop to register.Payments via the QR Code system (Scan and Pay) among others will be quick to facilitate shopping, simplify life and save valuable time. In addition, the Prime Minister Pravind Jugnauth was present at the launch of the My.T Money service. He declared, “The government’s vision is to make our country a digital economy. I am glad that this service sticks to our philosophy.’’Source: NexTVAfrica.com.